node.text:
Pompadour is embarrassing to watch. Complete whack job. It’s funny to watch someone speak as the thoughts actually come in their head, and he’s making it up as he goes along. It’s like I can see his brain cells clicking together. And apparently him yelling, “we know who you are,” you will never be allowed in public again,” “you better watch out,” wasn’t supposed to be a threat. My eyes  rolled so far back in my head when he said that, I could see my brand new jeans. 

He says that he said that because the guy they were harassing almost hit a child on the way out. I call bullshit on that, but just a few months ago they were really excited about people being able to run over protesters in the street. #PickALane #HeDoesntEvenGoHere @thetnholler

Everyone should be following @thetnholler  He is absolutely my favorite Instagram account. Always the first place I check everyday. 

And I can tell you first hand that not everyone in Tennessee is a “bumpkin,” but you’d never know it by watching this clip. Embarrassing ourselves daily, and she’s on the damn school board. 

Repost @thetnholler with @get.repost
・・・
CHATTANOOGA DAD: “What should parents of cancer patients do (without a mask mandate)?” 

SCHOOL BOARD MEMBER RHONDA THURMAN: “I don’t know… I can’t be take care of 40,000 kids.” 

NOOGA DAD: “Isn’t that your job??” 

All good questions. @NoogaHoller 😷 @govbilllee

node.text:
You know how you have this band you love and you go and see them a lot and it’s just feels like it’s just you and the band and then all the sudden everybody catches on to how amazing they are and then all then one day, BOOM! There’s a gazillion people at their shows?

That’s how I think of @justinkanew  He’s this amazing Williamson County guy, that we met when he was running for office. We didn’t even ask him what happened to the passports. #AmazingRace 

We just loved him to pieces, and now everybody is catching wind of this amazing Tennessee treasure. We need more ppl like Justin Kanew! #JustinKanew

“Speaking takes all of Sechler's energy. He's no longer on an ECMO machine or ventilator. He has oxygen but is very weak. He can't walk and has lost much of his muscle.

Sechler wanted to share his story to encourage people to get vaccinated and wear masks.

"I didn't have preexisting conditions," he said. "[I'm] 43 years old. I'm not overweight. I know that people want their freedom. I know that there's a point of contention. But I'm telling you, do not end up like me. You will regret it."

I posted the accompanying article on my Twitter @AGirlHasNoPres More @newschannel5

node.text:
Pompadour is embarrassing to watch. Complete whack job. It’s funny to watch someone speak as the thoughts actually come in their head, and he’s making it up as he goes along. It’s like I can see his brain cells clicking together. And apparently him yelling, “we know who you are,” you will never be allowed in public again,” “you better watch out,” wasn’t supposed to be a threat. My eyes  rolled so far back in my head when he said that, I could see my brand new jeans. 

He says that he said that because the guy they were harassing almost hit a child on the way out. I call bullshit on that, but just a few months ago they were really excited about people being able to run over protesters in the street. #PickALane #HeDoesntEvenGoHere @thetnholler

node.text:
One of Tennessee’s own. This is from the same county where all those ppl threatened folks coming out of the school board meeting who wanted kids to wear masks. 

It will be interesting to see how cops handle cops, for beating cops. 

“Ronald Colton McAbee, a 27-year-old Williamson County sheriff's deputy, was arrested Aug. 17 after the FBI received a tip he was the man in officer-worn body camera footage who attempted to fight a Metropolitan Police Department officer and drag another into the mob storming the Capitol.

McAbee is part of a seven-person indictment group all charged with assaulting officers on the day of the insurrection. His co-defendants included Jack Wade Whitton, who is accused of using a crutch to attack an MPD officer, and Jeffrey Sabol, who is accused of holding a baton across an officer's neck.”

#RonaldColtonMcAbee #WilliamsonCounty #Tennessee #Terrorist
